headline: ON Semiconductor (ON) Is Up 10.8% After AI-fueled Semiconductor Rally and Strong Earnings — Has The Bull Case Changed?
summary: Shares of ON Semiconductor and other chipmakers surged recently as a broader rally in the semiconductor sector was fueled by optimism around artificial intelligence technologies and strong earnings reported by leading companies like Taiwan Semiconductor. This wave of positive sentiment has pushed the Philadelphia Semiconductor Index to record highs, reflecting the market's enthusiasm for AI-driven demand and its potential impact on companies throughout the semiconductor supply chain. headline: Stock Index Futures Muted With Focus on Corporate Earnings
summary: December S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESZ25) are down -0.04%, and December Nasdaq 100 E-Mini futures (NQZ25) are down -0.08% this morning, pointing to a muted open on Wall Street after yesterday’s rally, as investors await a fresh batch of corporate earnings reports, with a particular focus on results from blue chips such as Netflix, Coca-Cola, and 3M.
